  <!-- What this site is -->
  <div class="prose-block">
    <h2>What good.vibes.diy is</h2>
    <p>Vibes DIY is for making tiny custom software — things built for your specific situation, your specific people. A trivia night for the group chat, or an order form that takes payments for the shop. The same move either way: you make the thing; it ships. good.vibes.diy is the public gallery of what people are making with it.</p>
    <p>The site is organized around audiences and topics: pages for <a href="teachers.html">teachers</a>, <a href="coaches.html">coaches</a>, <a href="engineers.html">engineers</a>, <a href="homeschoolers.html">homeschoolers</a>, and more each show a curated cluster of apps built specifically for that use case. The <a href="edu/index.html">Edu section</a> has 22 subject clusters grounded in <a href="edu/syllabi.html">real university syllabi</a> — <a href="edu/about.html">read about the approach</a>. <a href="expressions/index.html">Expressions pages</a> explore more personal, ambient, and experimental uses. Every app is deployed on the <a href="https://links.vibes.diy/homepage">Vibes DIY platform</a> — not a mockup, not a prototype.</p>
    <p>The goal is to show what specific people actually made — for their night, their group, their shop, their weird specific situation. If you see something useful, open it. If you see something close to what you need, clone it and make it yours.</p>
  </div>

